    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ h(r) = {\frac{r^{3}-36r}{r^{3}+16r^{2}+60r}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>h(r)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{r-6}{r+10}, r\ne -6\hbox{ and }r\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   h(r) \amp = {\frac{r^{3}-36r}{r^{3}+16r^{2}+60r}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}-36\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+16r+60\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-6\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+10\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{r-6}{r+10}, r\ne -6\hbox{ and }r\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>r(r+6)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>r \ne {-6, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
